outing, caching, and evaluation themes.","The existing summary anchors the profile in architecture and delivery rather than research framing, which is directionally correct for this category."],"underrepresented_now":["Architect-family title positioning is weaker than the underlying evidence base because the current headline is generic and the stronger architect-title variants remain upstream.","Stakeholder-facing advisory, business translation, and subject-matter-expert signals are not surfaced with enough prominence for this category.","Governance, guardrails, structured outputs, evaluation, and safe-production AI controls are present in curated project evidence but not elevated in the current summary/headline.","Player-coach leadership is present, but the representation does not cleanly distinguish it from management-heavy leadership language.","Transferable architecture depth from Samdock and earlier distributed-systems roles is underweighted relative to tool-centric AI skills."],"overstated_risk_now":["'Engineering Leader' in the current headline can read more management-heavy than the actual evidence warrants for this category.","The skills-priority layer leans heavily into RAG and tooling names, which risks obscuring the stronger architecture, reliability, and governance signals.","Because the representation is proxy-derived, the current summary may overfit one flagship modernization story and understate the candidate's broader architecture portfolio."],"representation_priorities":["Reframe the headline toward architect-first AI/platform leadership using current safe titles and architecture language.","Rewrite the summary so it balances modernization, operational readiness, stakeholder translation, and production AI governance rather than relying on a single legacy-transformation paragraph.","Reorder project emphasis to foreground platform scope, guardrails, evaluation, reliability, and operational readiness before tool inventories.","Bring forward one stakeh